# Pathline work ownership

## Orchestration

- Multi-step or multi-surface work starts with **`pathline-orchestrator`** (see `.cursor/skills/pathline-orchestration/SKILL.md`).
- One agent per exclusive path set per wave. If ownership is unclear, stop and re-assign — do not dual-edit.

## Exclusive lanes (do not cross)

| Work | Owner agent | Forbidden for that agent |
|------|-------------|--------------------------|
| Coordination | pathline-orchestrator | Product UI / Figma node writes |
| Figma | pathline-figma-design | `client/`, `desktop/`, `services/` |
| Shell/nav | five-surface-nav-shell | Path/Accounts/Vault page bodies |
| Path Library | five-surface-path-library | Accounts/Vault persistence |
| Accounts+Vault | five-surface-accounts-vault | Shell nav rewrite |
| Dashboard/System | five-surface-dashboard-system | Path EditForm / Run engine |
| UX upgrade brief | pathline-ux-upgrade | Figma MCP |

## Stack / IA locks

- React + Radix + shadcn + Tailwind + Tauri only.
- Five surfaces; Edit/Run panels inside Path Library; secrets never in Path JSON.

## Figma free / Starter

- Prefer **one** Figma file with pages.
- Skip Code Connect, Dev Mode redlines, and published team libraries unless the user confirms a paid plan.
- Handoff via screenshots / `get_design_context` + component-name annotations.
